Having collected his darts, Cody moved toward the other side of the room, giving a wide berth to the open passageway.
As he did so, Lulu appeared, apparently recovered from her surprise. The little dog immediately laid into the fox,
savagely tearing at the corpse and bolting down bite after bite. "You're a hungry girl, aren't you?" Cody
said. Something about the scene made him vaguely uncomfortable -- perhaps it was the sight of the dog eating another
animal so similar in shape, or perhaps just Lulu's blood-streaked muzzle and the flying gobbets of flesh.
